{#-
Shared Jinja macro for the post-task-creation "Continue / Save for later"
decision-point block. Consumed via {% from "_auto_continue_block.j2" import auto_continue_block %}
in 4 skills (aitask-explore, aitask-fold, aitask-pr-import, aitask-revert).

The IF arm fires when `profile.explore_auto_continue == true` (no committed
profile sets this) — verbiage matches the pre-t777_28 inline blocks. The
ELSE arm renders the AskUserQuestion with per-skill parameters.

Parameters:
  question                Full AskUserQuestion `Question:` string.
  continue_description    The "Continue to implementation" option description.
  continue_target         Where "Continue to implementation" jumps in the ELSE
                          arm (e.g. "the handoff below", "Step 6", "Step 7").
  inform_filename         Filename template embedded in the Save-for-later
                          "Inform user" line, e.g. "t<N>_<name>.md".
  inform_label            Leading word in the Save-for-later Inform-user line
                          (i.e. "<inform_label> <inform_filename> is ready.").
                          Default: "Task". aitask-revert overrides to
                          "Revert task" to match its rendered output.
  inform_pick_arg         The argument passed to /aitask-pick in the Inform
                          user line (e.g. "<N>", "<primary_id>").
                          Default: "<N>".
  default_option          "continue" (Continue-first) or "save" (Save-first,
                          PR-import). Default: "continue".
  post_options_note       Optional skill-specific note rendered between the
                          Options list and the "If" sections. Empty string
                          means no note. Default: "".
  feedback_skill_name     If non-empty, emit a Satisfaction Feedback
                          Procedure call on the Save-for-later branch with
                          this skill_name. Default: "" (no feedback call).

Whitespace contract: the macro return begins and ends with `\n`, so the
call-site renders cleanly as one block inside the surrounding skill body.
See `aidocs/framework/skill_authoring_conventions.md` "Jinja templating in skills"
for the macro-placement convention and the broader dedup rules.
-#}
{%- macro auto_continue_block(question, continue_description, continue_target, inform_filename, inform_label="Task", inform_pick_arg="<N>", default_option="continue", post_options_note="", feedback_skill_name="") %}
{% if profile.explore_auto_continue is defined and profile.explore_auto_continue -%}
- Display: "Profile '{{ profile.name }}': continuing to implementation"
- Skip the AskUserQuestion below and proceed directly to the handoff
{%- else -%}
Use `AskUserQuestion`:
- Question: "{{ question }}"
- Header: "Proceed"
- Options:
{%- if default_option == "save" %}
  - "Save for later" (description: "Task saved — pick it up later with /aitask-pick <N>")
  - "Continue to implementation" (description: "{{ continue_description }}")
{%- else %}
  - "Continue to implementation" (description: "{{ continue_description }}")
  - "Save for later" (description: "Task saved — pick it up later with /aitask-pick <N>")
{%- endif %}

{% if post_options_note -%}
{{ post_options_note }}

{% endif -%}
**If "Save for later":**
- Inform user: "{{ inform_label }} {{ inform_filename }} is ready. Run `/aitask-pick {{ inform_pick_arg }}` when you want to implement it."
{%- if feedback_skill_name %}
- Execute the **Satisfaction Feedback Procedure** (see `.claude/skills/task-workflow/satisfaction-feedback.md`) with `skill_name` = `"{{ feedback_skill_name }}"`.
{%- endif %}
- End the workflow.

**If "Continue to implementation":**
- Proceed to {{ continue_target }}.
{% endif %}
{%- endmacro -%}
